Anyone recognize this baby? 
Breaking the highlight reel momentarily to tell a little story & keep it real.
Wednesday morning, my work computer crashed. Don’t worry, client work is backed up in multiple places but guess who’s photos aren’t…
Cue the cold sweats. Friday, Reed’s car was broken into and MY credit card was stolen out of the center console- (of course I didn’t put it there, but we won’t talk about that) - good times. Well, the good times were had by the guy that bought all the Patron (not a joke) on my dime but I digress:: 
Last night my computer 🖥️ was brought back to life by superhero @snowskinc 🦸‍♂️(if you’re local to Bham)! Thankful doesn’t describe it. 

I tell all of this because look at what I found. 
My baby boy- who turns 11 on Wednesday. ELEVEN. His newborn photos that I never finished editing. I am sure I edited one for his announcement and figured I’d get to the rest of them when things slowed down. But guess what guys- things never slow down. 

Yesterday, I started backing up years worth of images and sent a copy to my husband, mom and sister just in case. I know my kids will want these! I cannot believe that I let some of these images sit on a computer for a decade. Make sure every photo is backed up in multiple places. Print them. 
Something I do for everyone else, yet I didn’t take the time to do it for myself. 
Anyway- this year, I’ve found my resolution… practice what I preach… protect these tangible memories, my friends. I was sick over the thought of losing them. 
Cheers to a new week, thinking this one’s gotta be better 😉❤️

I think everyone here will agree that this week was both a literal and figurative cold plunge coming off of last week’s pjs-till-noon-vibe. 

Guys, there is no way I’ll ever catch up on this app. Doing the actual WORK takes up all my time these days. Fall was great. It was busy and when I wasn’t shooting I was moonlighting as an unpaid Uber driver. I got a cool car trash can… maybe I’ll link it. 🤪

That said - I am excited for 2024. And if it’s anything like 2023, that means I won’t have too much time to post… but I promise I’m still here behind the scenes, giving it my all one more year ❤️👊🏻📸

Oh. 
PS: In true fashion, I didn’t have time to post the annual Giveaway at Christmas. So pay attention! It’s coming over the next few days! 😉
